          <fr:mainmatter><html:p>In the case of an <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00JF.xml" title="path in a directed graph" addr="jms-00JF" type="local">endo-relation</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R\in \mathrm {Rel}{\mathopen {}\left ({\mathopen {}\left  [n\right  ]\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>, the <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00JH.xml" title="the reflexive-transitive closure of an endo-relation" addr="jms-00JH" type="local">reflexive-transitive closure</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R^{\circ *}]]></fr:tex> can be computed using a finite union rather over <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[m \leq  n]]></fr:tex> rather than an infinite union over all of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {N}]]></fr:tex>; in particular, we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R^{\circ *} = \bigcup _{k \leq  n} R^{\circ  k}]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
 
   
